<seg id="2">Preface</seg>
<seg id="3">The declaration of Lima, which was adopted in 1977, emphasises that the courts of auditors are empowered to examine the entire public finances.</seg>
<seg id="4">The declaration calls for the courts to have the power to examine the tax collection as broadly as possible.</seg>
<seg id="5">The organisation of the European top audit authorities (EUROSAI) considers taxes to be an important part of public revenue.</seg>
<seg id="6">The thematic focus of the VI. EUROSAI Congress, which took place in Bonn in 2005, was the audit of public revenue by the courts of auditors.</seg>
<seg id="7">One of the most important steps on the road to optimising the testing activity of a Court of Auditors is to draw up a special strategy for examining public revenue.</seg>
<seg id="8">This applies in particular to taxes as the largest source of public revenue with a high risk of default.</seg>
<seg id="9">As national economies are increasingly interlinked and interdependent, there can be a situation in which national courts of auditors can only carry out their examination activities in cooperation with the courts of auditors of other states.</seg>
<seg id="10">As an example, the examination of international organised fraud can be considered, which can lead to significant loss of revenue in many countries.</seg>
<seg id="11">In the fight against such crimes, cooperation between the authorities is required.</seg>
<seg id="12">The Court of Auditors, which examines in this area, must be prepared to cooperate closely.</seg>
<seg id="13">The idea for an examination of the value added tax and the MIAS system is VI. EUROSAI congress was created in Bonn. This review was carried out in cooperation between the Court of Auditors of the Czech Republic and the German Federal Court of Auditors.</seg>
<seg id="14">In the course of a thorough preparation, the relevant courts of auditors had to first familiarise themselves with the legal framework and the VAT management procedures in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="15">Due to the evaluation of this information, we presented the selection of the examination items for the examination planning.</seg>
