<seg id="17">We are convinced that the results of our review will not only contribute to improving the work of financial management, but will also be the basis for a proposal on an improved system of international exchange of information.</seg>
<seg id="18">Report on the results of the parallel review of the management of the turnover tax of the Czech Republic and Germany</seg>
<seg id="19">Einführung</seg>
<seg id="20">A file mark: CZ) 06/27 (DE) VIII 2 – 2005 – 1215</seg>
<seg id="21">The subject of examination:</seg>
<seg id="22">(CZ) Management of VAT after the accession of the Czech Republic to the European Union</seg>
<seg id="23">(DE) Review for the cooperation of administrative authorities in the field of VAT in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 of the Council and 1925/2004</seg>
<seg id="24">the Commission's examination objective:</seg>
<seg id="25">(CZ) The aim of the examination in the Czech Republic was to investigate the procedures applied by the financial management in the field of value added tax following the integration of the Czech Republic into the common internal market of the European Community (hereinafter referred to as “EG”) with free movement of goods and services, as well as the use of the MIAS1, in particular the control of the use of VAT exemption for intra-Community deliveries.</seg>
<seg id="26">(DE) The aim of the examination was to investigate the system of intra-Community sales tax control with a focus on official assistance in the field of VAT in accordance with the above regulations.</seg>
<seg id="27">As a result of the audit, weaknesses should be highlighted and recommendations on their remedying should be made.</seg>
<seg id="28">VAT information exchange system The examinations were carried out jointly by the Court of Auditors of the Czech Republic (“NKÚ”) and the Federal Republic of Germany (“BRH”) of the Federal Republic of Germany on the basis of an agreement concluded on 8 June 2006.</seg>
<seg id="29">The focus of cooperation was the review of selected business events between entrepreneurs from the Czech Republic and the Federal Republic of Germany, the utilisation of information obtained from international assistance between the financial administrations and the comparison of VAT management systems in the two states.</seg>
<seg id="30">A joint final report on the results of the tests was drawn up in the spirit of the European guideline No 31 for the implementation of INTOSAI testing standards.</seg>
<seg id="31">The tested period included the period from 1 May 2004 to 31 December 2005.</seg>
<seg id="32">Summary of the results and evaluation of parallel testing</seg>
<seg id="33">The parallel review of VAT management in the Czech Republic and Germany was carried out on the basis of an agreement between the two courts of auditors.</seg>
<seg id="34">In addition to the focus on the exchange of information in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 of the Council and 1925/2004 of the Commission, other closely related aspects have also been examined, such as the registration of taxable persons, tax declarations and summary reports.</seg>
<seg id="35">In addition, the examination also extended to the legal situation in cross-border passenger transport with bus and coach transport and the comparison of statistical data.</seg>
<seg id="36">Comparison of VAT administrations in the two states has identified differences in the following areas:</seg>
<seg id="37">1) Registration for purposes of value added tax.</seg>
