<seg id="554">4.5.3 Management of VAT exam at large-scale companies</seg>
<seg id="555">In accordance with what has been agreed, both courts of auditors have not examined individual cases. They have looked into the question of how the financial administrations are acting in the USt test of large-scale enterprises.</seg>
<seg id="556">With the help of a questionnaire, they gathered information in the financial administrations that are essential for examining large companies.</seg>
<seg id="557">• What statistical records and evaluations of the USt test of large-scale companies are the management of the tax administration available?</seg>
<seg id="558">In particular:</seg>
<seg id="559">• Are there statistics or records of the extent to which a distinction is made between USt fraud and general USt check?</seg>
<seg id="560">CZ: No, the current version of the ATIS system does not allow such distinction.</seg>
<seg id="561">Germany: The financial management does not distinguish between audits for combating USt fraud and general USt checks.</seg>
<seg id="562">• Are there statistics or records of the time close to the tests?</seg>
<seg id="563">CZ: The ATIS system collects information on the time proximity of tests intra-Community acquisition of selected U.S.</seg>
<seg id="564">The same applies to information about the beginning and end of the examination of the FA.</seg>
<seg id="565">Germany: No, the statistics for auditors summarised at federal level contain only information on the so-called average last audit period (year).</seg>
<seg id="566">This figure gives no overview of the audit periods selected for individual companies.</seg>
<seg id="567">U.S. special auditors focus on the last US-executive periods and are also empowered to examine large-scale companies.</seg>
<seg id="568">The statistics for USt special auditors led at federal level do not contain any information on the size class of the tested company.</seg>
<seg id="569">• Are there statistics or records of the type of multi-face; e.g. B. divided into:</seg>
<seg id="570">i. real additional result (e.g. Application of a reduced instead of the general US rate)</seg>
<seg id="571">ii. A lot of additional results (e.g. B. Verification/representation of a non-referential situation in another tax period)</seg>
<seg id="572">iii. Cash-effectiveness (payment of the prescribed additional result)</seg>
<seg id="573">CZ:</seg>
<seg id="574">The Czech financial management monitors the number of tax audits carried out, the level of the tax revenue broken down according to tax types, the number of certified taxable persons and the number of tax periods tested.</seg>
<seg id="575">Other tax procedures (the investigations on the ground, reminders) are monitored in the same way.</seg>
<seg id="576">Irrespective of this, the amount of repayments and the receipt of payment are recorded.</seg>
<seg id="577">Statistics on tax debt are broken down according to tax cards. However, it is not distinguished between tax debts that have arisen as a result of tax returns and those arising from the FA's audits.</seg>
<seg id="578">Germany: No, the statistics collected at federal level for auditors and USt special auditors do not distinguish according to the above criteria.</seg>
<seg id="579">Most financial authorities, where local surveys have been made, are also differentiated in this respect.</seg>
<seg id="580">• Will the results of the audit be recorded?</seg>
<seg id="581">CZ: Yes, the FA can select test cases based on criteria linked to selected indicators stored in the ATIS system.</seg>
<seg id="582">Germany: There are no regulations at federal level.</seg>
<seg id="583">Accordingly, the statistics for auditors and USt special auditors compiled at federal level do not provide such information.</seg>
<seg id="584">However, the finance ministries of the Federal Government and the Länder have agreed on a common approach.</seg>
<seg id="585">So, in the event of exceeding a certain threshold in ZAUBER, auditors and tax traders of the countries have entered the tax revenue they have achieved in the event of a certain threshold.</seg>
<seg id="586">In this case, additional information must be provided, e.g. B. via the origin of the USt majority.</seg>
<seg id="587">• What are the most common observations?</seg>
<seg id="588">CZ:</seg>
<seg id="589">- Large-scale taxable companies have unjustifiably used pre-tax deduction for delivered deliveries and services;</seg>
