<seg id="617">5. Conclusions</seg>
<seg id="618">The cooperation between the two courts of auditors has proved its worth.</seg>
<seg id="619">In this way, necessary knowledge of the systems applied in both countries could be obtained: this applies in particular: • internal community sales, • risk management in the USt, particularly with regard to the selection of risky sales, • the recovery of US-Treaches and • US-Proliferation of large-scale enterprises.</seg>
<seg id="620">The test laid down differences in the strategies for detecting USt fraud and the systems explained above.</seg>
<seg id="621">These findings can be used to improve the existing procedures.</seg>
<seg id="622">They can also be used to initiate a discussion among the interested authorities, which can be used to carry out audit approaches and strategies for combating fraud. This applies e.g. for the relationship within and between the Member States and the EU Commission.</seg>
<seg id="623">The experience and knowledge gained are intended to encourage the management of the USt in the future.</seg>
